post_text:
Dear PESD Families,

I am excited to announce that the county has met the benchmarks for safely opening schools for in-person learning! The school board met this evening, and we have set our opening date for Wednesday, September 9th. Our teachers will provide students with independent activities to do online on Tuesday (8/8) in order to spend the day making final preparations to safely welcome their in-person students back into their classrooms. There will be no GoogleMeets on Tuesday, September 8th.

Please look for an email from your school tomorrow morning with more details regarding your learning options as we move into this phase of opening schools.

Thank you!

post_text:
From all of us in the Palominas School District,

We want to wish you a safe and happy summer! While we, sadly, cannot offer summer school this year, we will be providing our summer meal service during the month of June. Please see our website and Facebook pages for summer food service bus routes and details. We will be working on our plans for reopening our schools for the 2020-2021 school year as we learn more from our state and local agencies. We will also be working on promotion celebrations if at all possible. Updates and opportunities for input will be provided throughout the summer, so please stay tuned to your school and district Facebook pages and look for our emails. Take care, have fun, and stay safe until we see you again!
text:
From all of us in the Palominas School District,

We want to wish you a safe and happy summer! While we, sadly, cannot offer summer school this year, we will be providing our summer meal service during the month of June. Please see our website and Facebook pages for summer food service bus routes and details. We will be working on our plans for reopening our schools for the 2020-2021 school year as we learn more from our state and local agencies. We will also be working on promotion celebrations if at all possible. Updates and opportunities for input will be provided throughout the summer, so please stay tuned to your school and district Facebook pages and look for our emails. Take care, have fun, and stay safe until we see you again!

shared_text:
Cochise County School Superintendent
May 21 at 3:23 PM ·

We, along with UArizona Cochise County Cooperative Extension (Building Healthy Communities and SNAP Ed) and the Cochise County Health Department are pleased to present Palominas Elementary School District as the winner of the 2020 School Health and Wellness Award!

Congratulations to all of the students, parents, School Staff, and community members who worked to make Palominas ESD an example of school wellness in Cochise County!

We, along with UArizona Cochise County Cooperative Extension (Building Healthy Communities and SNAP Ed) and the Cochise County Health Department are pleased to present Palominas Elementary School District as the winner of the 2020 School Health and Wellness Award!

post_text: Starting on March 30, 2020, the Palominas District buses will be delivering breakfast and lunch at bus stops. Please take a look at the document to find your child(s) food drop off time, for any of our preschool, elementary, and high school students as they are all eligible to meet the bus. Please be advised that most of the buses will more likely run late due to making sure we are at each of the stops and that students that are there get food. PLEASE pass this along, share it, talk about and help us get the word out to our families!! Any questions please call.

post_text:
Dear Palominas Parents and Community,
Please see Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman’s letter below regarding school closures. We will be remaining closed until April 10th. I would imagine that this may be subject to change. We are meeting with all of our staffs on Monday morning to determine the best ways to continue instruction, during the closure. As soon as we have our plans in place we will be communicating them to you. The health and safety of our students, families, and community are priority number one for all of us in the Palominas District. Thank you for your patience as we move through this together!
shared_text:
AZGOVERNOR.GOV
Open Letter To Arizona Families, Educators, School Leaders, And Education Community Members
text:
Dear Palominas Parents and Community,
Please see Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman’s letter below regarding school closures. We will be remaining closed until April 10th. I would imagine that this may be subject to change. We are meeting with all of our staffs on Monday morning to determine the best ways to continue instruction, during the closure. As soon as we have our plans in place we will be communicating them to you. The health and safety of our students, families, and community are priority number one for all of us in the Palominas District. Thank you for your patience as we move through this together!

AZGOVERNOR.GOV
Open Letter To Arizona Families, Educators, School Leaders, And Education Community Members

post_text: We are so proud of our amazing preschool team!
shared_text:
Valley View School
September 26, 2019 at 9:41 PM ·

Congratulations to our Valley View Preschool for winning 1st Place in the preschool category for the Best Of The Vista & Tombstone.

The Herald mentioned us: Valley View Preschool in Palominas came in first in the Best of Preschools category and director Della Thompson, a 19-year veteran teacher, could not be more surprised.

She leads a three teacher, five paraprofessional team who look after 60 children. “We have such a dynamic team here,” she said. “We have a lot of resources here in the Palominas school district. Our staff provides whatever it takes to give each of the kids what they need to learn.”

post_text: We had quite a bit to celebrate at our monthly governing board meeting on Tuesday. First, we celebrated several staff members for their longevity with the district as we recognized service of up to 30 years! Additionally, we wished Mrs. Copeland, our outgoing superintendant farewell as she will be retiring this summer after 27 years of service to children. Next, we were treated to a presentation from our Gifted and Talented Education program on their collaborative project to build a playhouse. Finally, Mrs. Lucero presented on the achievements of the district cyber Patriot teams.

Palominas Elementary School is at Palominas Elementary School.
March 27, 2019 at 12:42 PM · Hereford, AZ ·

The technology in our classrooms is not a toy but a way for teachers to enhance the learning process through collaborative interactive explorative processes. Here, in Mrs. White's 2nd grade class, students are working in teams to measure the length of rectangles on a shared page and then recording their findings on the interactive whiteboard. Technology used this way promotes student engagement and strengthens understanding and cooperation.

March 27, 2019 at 12:42 PM · Hereford, AZ ·

The technology in our classrooms is not a toy but a way for teachers to enhance the learning process through collaborative interactive explorative processes. Here, in Mrs. White's 2nd grade class, students are working in teams to measure the length of rectangles on a shared page and then recording their findings on the interactive whiteboard. Technology used this way promotes student engagement and strengthens understanding and cooperation.

post_text:
Dear Palominas District Families,

We received notification today from Edupoint, the company who produces our student information system (Synergy) and the ParentVue and StudentVue Apps, that there is an issue with a recent release of StudentVue. Essentially, some android users are experiencing a popup when they access the app that asks them if they are at school today, if they are safe, and where they are. According to Edupoint, this is an emergency protocol that should not have been launched. Until we receive word from Edupoint that this issue is resolved, we have disabled StudentVue. ParentVue is not impacted. If your child has an Android phone and uses StudentVue, please make sure that they update the application regularly. We apologize for any inconvenience that this may have caused.

Sincerely,

The Palominas District Leadership Team

Palominas School District #49 will begin the process of destroying special education records and speech/language records for students of Palominas School District born in 1993, 1994, and 1995. The destruction of records will begin in January 2019.

Before these records are destroyed, parents or former students have the right to review them and obtain copies of this information as it may be needed for other purposes, such as documentation of eligibility for social security benefits, etc.

Please contact us in writing at the following address if you would like to obtain copies of your child’s records. Please include date of birth, phone number, and address.

Hereford, AZ 85615

Coronado Elementary School
October 16, 2018 at 2:11 PM ·

Coronado Elementary School has implemented "Operation Positivity"

The focus of the project is:
Spreading positivity through school and learning environment
Getting support from the students, teachers, staff, parents, community and administrators
Community and family engagement
Creating an environment that inspires children and adults to be kind and positive to all people
Surrounding all of the Coronado family in positivity
Most of all-to make people happy!

Thank you to Team lead- Casey Bell! Thank you to Kim Galarneau, Maria Andruszka, Teri Mendez, Marissa Herrera, Jenny Thrasher and all of the wonderful staff and volunteers that worked during Fall Break to complete it! Attached are photos of their first project.

The plan is to expand the project, to include the hallways and common areas.

Dear Palominas Community,

Please be aware that the Summer Food Program starts June 4th and runs weekdays through June 29th. During this time, children 18 and younger are provided breakfast and lunch free of charge. Breakfast will be served at 8:30 and lunch will be served at noon. If adults would like to join their children for meals, breakfast will cost $1.00 and lunch will cost $2.65.

Dear Palominas Community,

Please be aware that the Summer Food Program starts June 4th and runs weekdays through June 29th. During this time, children 18 and younger are provided breakfast and lunch free of charge. Breakfast will be served at 8:30 and lunch will be served at noon. If adults would like to join their children for meals, breakfast will cost $1.00 and lunch will cost $2.65.

The Palominas District Band traveled to San Dimas, California this past weekend to participate in the Forum Music Festival. They played two pieces for the audience and two judges and were rated according to a national standard.
The band was rated GOLD, which puts them in the top 10% of middle school bands in the country!! This rating marks the end of a perfect "season" for the band who also received a Platinum rating at the AZ Pageant of he Bands in Glendale Arizonan in April. Congratulations to the Melanie Godwin and the Palominas District Band for an excellent year!

shared_text:
Coronado Elementary School is feeling proud.
April 28, 2018 at 5:26 PM · Sierra Vista, AZ ·

The Coronado CyberPatriot team has completed their 2017-18 season. They placed 1st in the state, advanced to the national Semifinals, and today they took 1st in the Cochise College President’s Cup Challenge to bring the trophy back to the Palominas School District. The team is comprised of Caleb Russian, Josh Asato, Erin Posey, Joe Valenzuela, and Michael Stanley.
